@gavinandresen  can you try running 

(for i in {1..220000} ; do export bh=`./bitcoind getblockhash $i` ; for tx in `./bitcoind getblock $bh | grep '     "' | cut -d'"' -f2` ; do  ./bitcoind getrawtransaction $tx > /dev/null  ; done   ; done)

On a OSX mainnet node with this patch and txindex=1 when you get a chance?  It should causes about 500 FDs to be used.

